Full Description: G³ is a SaaS company. It produces a sophisticated package for consultants and accountants to enable them to use the company's proprietary audit technology and associated support services to conduct in depth, surgical diagnostic evaluations of companies' operations, financials and structure to determine where companies are out of balance and sluggish. That Audit  package is the foundation for the consultant to assist the company in correcting its operational behaviors that are contributing to earnings stagnation or erosion, getting them ""cleaned up"" and on a solid footing for either sale or growth. All services and programs are anchored by the company's revolutionary corporate audit, the Accelerated Value Diagnostic (AVD) based on the highly successful audit product the founder developed for the environmental assessment industry. The original version like the ones  in development, is process driven, standardized and dissects a company into 50 Key Performance Indicators (KPIs), with each being scientifically analyzed for its contribution to EBITDA erosion and then ranks, by a sophisticated algorithm, from high to low the worst to the least problem areas. All inputs done online and report auto generated. There are an additional 9 versions in development.  The company's SaaS target market is large, consisting of business consultants, accountants and similar type of professionals who work with companies dealing with their financials and operations.  Likewise, the Business Advisors who are licensed through the model, have a larger market which is all companies, all governmental agencies and all not for profit organizations.   The company also licenses the AVD to large private companies and consulting firms. G3 currently has it corporate office, regional vice presidents and 10 business development directors in place in addition to 50 founding business advisors. Description: Atjeu Hosting is part of Atjeu Publishing LLC and is dedicated to internet hosting and colocation.
Full Description: Atjeu Hosting is part of Atjeu Publishing LLC and is dedicated to internet hosting and colocation. Originally founded in 1989, Atjeu Publishing LLC entered the internet market in 1995 with the prolific start of the World Wide Web (WWW). Initially Atjeu did website design exclusively, but quickly expanded into the hosting side of the business allowing Atjeu to provide total package solutions to their customers, Atjeu began offering shared/virtual hosting. As the hosting side of the business grew, the administration at Atjeu became less and less satisfied with the quality of service it was receiving from its co-location providers. The situation continued to deteriorate regardless of who Atjeu was using. Since Atjeu has very high standards in regards to technical support, quality of bandwidth and quality of service and did not want to compromise this service to its customers, Atjeu had to make a change. Unable to find a reasonably priced high quality co-location facility, Atjeu decided to build its own facility in order to have complete control over what it could provide to its customers in terms of both quality of service and product offerings. Today Atjeu’s facilities boast dedicated redundant fiber optic connections, only the highest quality Next-Gen bandwidth providers, and redundancy, redundancy, redundancy! At Atjeu, their motto has always been to know their customers by name. They like to maintain the small company atmosphere while at the same time providing reliable cutting edge hosting solutions to their customers. Many people are fed up with the big corporate atmosphere and huge companies that spring up overnight and disappear the next day. Atjeu is founded on financial principles that make sense; principles that should keep Atjeu around for the long haul. Many companies will spring up overnight and offer products and services well below their cost with the intention of selling their customer base within a short period of time. Most of these companies know full well they are not profitable and cannot continue to be a viable company in the long-term. That has never been the goal of Atjeu. Their goal is to build long term individual business relationships that stand the test of time and that are mutually beneficial to both their customers, your customers, and their respective companies profitability. Atjeu’s no-compromise attitude has led to Atjeu being one of the highest quality and yet still reasonably priced hosting companies on the internet today. Providing service to companies all around the globe, Atjeu is known for its quality tech support, friendly atmosphere, and high-speed redundant network. Your company and your customers will benefit from the quality and pricing of Atjeu’s services.

Description: Film Production Capital is a full-service tax credit brokerage company.
Full Description: Film Production Capital is a full-service tax credit brokerage company which specializes in state tax incentives for film, television, animation projects, digital interactive media (video games), music recording, commercials, live performances, festivals, and more. Film Production Capital began as a Louisiana-based tax credit brokerage in 2003 designed to monetize first-of-their-kind tax credits offered by the State of Louisiana to encourage motion picture production within its borders. Once the Louisiana tax credit model became successful, other states followed suit, and Film Production Capital grew along with them. The company has formidable expertise and institutional knowledge of all domestic tax incentive programs and maintains branches and personnel in key incentive jurisdictions such as Louisiana, Michigan, Georgia, and Puerto Rico. Film Production Capital offers strategic counseling to ensure productions choose the right jurisdiction for their project to maximize their return on investment. Once a jurisdiction is chosen, FPC provides a budget analysis, assists with the initial certification process and deal-structuring, and serves as an audit liaison to ensure final certification of tax credits. Furthermore, the company is actively involved in the legislative and rule-making process in order to safe-guard the incentive programs and protect Their  clients’ interests from the ever changing laws, regulations, policies and procedures.
